    "name": "Chunk 1/2",
    "doc_id": "edc0aa58c25a485a9c05c12750ec21aa",
    "text": "SKYC Project  \nClient requested for a strategic automation process through which customer data is regularly updated in adherence to Money Laundering Regulations.  \nIBM worked with Client to set up a strategic case management lifecycle as part of the SKYC (Smart KYC) project to support an enduring CDD and ID&amp;V journey, with flexibility to embed within the Event Based Monitoring (EBM) framework. As part of the project a Pega workflow management tool is being created to handle CDD and ID&amp;V workflow.  \nResults:  \n- Automated process of data collection and case management for CDD and ID&amp;V flows ensuring continued Regulatory compliance  \nIBM’s Delivery team streamlined the project’s planning and execution to ensure smooth coordination between Business and technical stakeholders. The project also involved IBM Business Analysts, SIT, and Non-Functional teams who worked on the successful delivery of the project. The Power BI reports built by the team helped Business to check the remediation status.  \n.co.uk Project  \nThe Customer Due Diligence (CDD) Remediation programme is designed to ensure compliance with Money Laundering Regulations (MLReg) obligations. It involves collecting missing CDD information and verifying that existing data is accurate and up-to-date. The existing approach captures customer details through Digital and Mediated channels.  \nThe image is a detailed flowchart illustrating a remediation process, likely for Customer Due Diligence (CDD) data.  \nThe process begins at the **CDD Cohort/FCCEP Remediation hub**. A key decision point asks: **\"Does member have an existing mediated channel prompt\"**?  \n*   If the answer is **No**, the process moves to **\"Invoke member on mediated channel\"**.\n*   If the answer is **Yes**, the process moves through steps involving **\"Member outreach Phase 1: Email and/or Letter\"** and providing **\"With link to co.uk portal & unique reference number\"**.  \nFollowing these initial steps, the member performs actions such as **\"Open DocuSign webform and enter URN & answer CDD questions\"**. The process also acknowledges **\"Other channels\"** including **\"Mediated Digital\"**.  \nThe next step requires the member to complete a **\"DocuSign form signed and submitted with personal & Customer CDD\"**. The diagram notes that the **\"DocuSign form is generic with no pre-populated fields\"**.  \nThe process continues with **\"Validate CDD Data provided\"**.  \nThe final steps involve the **\"RemOps team update data in CIS\"**.  \nResults:  \n- The solution enhances customer experience by providing  an easy and alternative way for a customer to share information\n- Improves Regulatory compliance  \nTo enhance client omni-channel strategy and improve customer engagement and completion rates, IBM is helping client build a new, reliable, and frictionless DocuSign solution on .co.uk. This alternative channel will allow client digitally inactive members to submit their CDD information without needing to visit a branch, use telephony services, or register for the Internet Bank or Mobile App. By broadening our approach, we aim to on increase overall participation and compliance through this journey.  \nID&amp;V Project - ID Remediation  \nThe ID&amp;V project involved enhancement of client ID&amp;V solution to use an automated process to directly upload Customer ID cases that successfully passed data validations to CIS. The Society entered into an agreement with Mitek systems to use their Verified Identity Platform for this purpose. Any records which did not pass the data validation were sent to the exceptional workflow tool for subsequent manual updation by the Remediation Operation team through the SAMM application.  \nThis image is a flowchart detailing a process workflow.  \nThe process begins with **Mitek**, which feeds into a process diamond labeled **Data Validations**.  \nFrom **Data Validations**, the process moves to the **ePaaS solution**, which is noted as **Fully automated (runs 24*7)**.  \n*   If the data **Pass**es through the **ePaaS solution**, it proceeds to a component labeled **BIP**.\n*   From **BIP**, an arrow points to a component labeled **CIS**.\n*   **BIP** and **SAMM** are connected, and an annotation states that **BIP failures come via DSA to EWT**.  \n*   If the process **Fails** at the **ePaaS solution**, it proceeds to **EWT**, which is contained within the **RemOps** section (indicated by a person icon).\n*   **EWT** is shown to send a failure/notification path to **SAMM**.  \nThe overall flow describes the journey from **Mitek** through **Data Validations** and the **ePaaS solution**, handling both successful paths (**Pass** -> **BIP** -> **CIS**) and failure paths (**Fails** -> **EWT** -> **SAMM**), while also noting the relationship between **BIP**, **SAMM**, and **DSA**.  \nResults:  \n- Digital method of customer identification reduced workload at client branches\n-  Increased convenience for overseas client customers\n-  Streamlined operations and increased productivity of the Remediation Operation team  \nIBM led the planning and execution of the project. Key requirements were gathered by IBM’s Business Analysts while the Development team validated the data between Mitek and CIS and also built an exception workflow tool for Operations.  Power BI reports built by the team enabled visibility into the remediation progress.  \nFurther, comprehensive testing by IBM’s SIT and Non-Functional teams ensured that both in-house and third-party components met quality, security, and performance standards for a smooth production rollout.  \nCDD Project  \nResults:  \n- Reduced workload of client branches and Telephony by providing a digital process to collect customer data  \nThe Customer Due Diligence (CDD) project was initiated to ensure that the customer data stored in client applications was correct. Customer information was requested based on either the ‘Periodic refresh’ risk rating of the customer or on the basis of ‘Invoke refresh ‘ i.e., account behaviour. The customer data could be updated through digital channels like Internet banking or the Banking App or through Mediated channels such as Branch or Telephony.  \nIBM’s Business Analysts were involved in Business requirement gathering for the project. The Data and Analytics team was involved in the following tasks:  \n1. CDD invoke - to trigger the functionality to gather information from customer\n2. CDD controls - to control the number of customer invoke to maintain the rate of customer request\n3. CDD Revoke and Reinvoke - this was required to prevent digital restriction on the customer, if customer had not shared the required information within 90 days  \nBusiness Savings Project (BuSa)  \nThe objective of this project was to establish a comprehensive and sustainable AML Remediation capability for Business Savings customers that ensured full compliance with the Financial Crime Minimum Control Standards  and the latest policy guidance. Client wanted to systematically address legacy compliance gaps by remediating the existing customer base through the collection and verification of missing Customer Due Diligence (CDD), and ID&amp;V documentation.",
